<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03140d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03140d">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03140d"> 140(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> right arm of illuminator / palladium </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Possibly from Theodore Edward Dowling, <cite>The Armenian Church</cite> (1910), p.50: &hellip; &ldquo;the destruction of the Cilicia kingdom, and in the year 1438, the right arm of St. Gregory, a relic which had become the palladium of the pontifical office, was transferred from Sis, the capital of that kingdom,&rdquo; <br><i>Lousavori&egrave;</i>, Illuminator, title given to St. Gregory (c.260-c.330). St. Gregory the Illuminator was the first Armenian patriarch, also known as the Apostle of Armenia. </mm> </dd></dl>
